\
\'93O my God!\'94 cried Ed Thatcher, clasping his hands.\
\
\'93You\'92d better go away for this evening, Mr. Thatcher.... She\'92ll quiet\
down, once you\'92ve gone.... I\'92ll put the roses in water.\'94\
\
On the last flight he caught up with a chubby man who was strolling\
