\'93Shall I bring in the milk?\'94\
\
\'93Oh do and sit down in the hall and I\'92ll call Ruth.\'94 The hall was very\
dark; smelled of sleep and toothpaste and massagecream; across one\
corner a cot still bore the imprint of a body on its rumpled sheets.\
Straw hats, silk eveningwraps, and a couple of men\'92s dress overcoats\
hung in a jostling tangle from the staghorns of the hatrack. Jimmy\
